_meanings:
{@--1@} Censuring, reviling; 
censure, reproach, blame, abuse;  
{#AstAtApavAdaBinnamaryAda#} <ls>U. 5</ls>; {#lokApavAdo#}
{#balavAnmato me#} <ls>R. 14. 40</ls>; {#lokApavAdAdBayaM#}
<ls>Bh. 2. 62</ls>; scandal, evil report;
{#cirakAlAnmayA SrutastavApavAdaH#} <ls>Pt. 1</ls>;
<ls>Ki. 11. 25</ls>, <ls n="Ki.">14. 12</ls>; <ls>Mk. 9. 3</ls>; <ls>U. 1</ls>;
<ls>Pt. 4</ls>; <ls>Y. 2. 207</ls>; {#devyAmapi hi vEdehyAM#}
{#sApavAdo yato janaH#} <ls>U. 1. 6</ls> 
spreading or indulging in scandals about;
{#na kevalaBatyAhitaM sApavAdamapi#} <ls>U. 2</ls>;
{#sApavAdaM#} censuringly <ls>Māl. 9.</ls>

{@--2@} An
exception, a special rule that 
restricts or sets aside a general rule
(<ab>opp.</ab> {#utsarga#}); {#mA hiMsyAtsarvaBUtAni iti#} 
{#utsargaH; vAyavyaM SvetamAlaBeta ityapavAdaH#};  
{#apavAdErivotsargAH kftavyAvfttayaH parEH#}  
<ls>Ku. 2. 27</ls>; <ls>R. 15. 7</ls>; {#°pratyayaH#} 
exceptional suffix; {#°sTalaM#} a case for a special
rule.

{@--4@} Refutation;
(in Vedānta <ab>phil.</ab>) refutation as of
a wrong imputation or belief;  
{#rajjuvivartasya sarpasya rajjumAtratvavat#}, 
{#vastuBUtabrahmaRo vivartasya prapaMcAdeH vastuBUtarUpatopadeSaH#}
{#apavAdaH#} <ls>Tv.</ls>; {#aDyAropApavAdAByAM#} 
{#vastutattvaviniScayaH#} <ls>Vedānta</ls>; hence also, a
means of refutation.

{@--7@} A
small bell or other instrument
sounded to decoy deer;  
{#maDukarErapavAdakarEriva#} <ls>Śi. 6. 9</ls>; ({#°karEH#} = {#vyADEH, apavAdaM#}
{#mfgavaMcanAya GaMwAdikutsitavAdyaMkurvaMti tEH#} <ls>Malli.</ls>)
